titles: An elegie upon the death of the most illustrious and victorious Prince Gustavus Adolphus King of Swethland &c. Composed immediately after the first rumours of his death, and now published and dedicated to the memoriall of so renouned a prince.
author: Russell, John, d. 1688.
notes: Verse - "What strange sad silence, doth the world astound?".
Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
keywords: Gustav, --  II, Adolf, --  King of Sweden, 1594-1632 --  Poetry --  Early works to 1800.
